## Code Review: PR #665 — Verdict: REQUEST_CHANGES

**2 required changes, 2 low-severity notes**

### Finding 1 (HIGH — Bug): `SnoozeMenu` has no click-outside dismissal
`BriefingPanel.tsx:58` — The popover has no backdrop or `mousedown` listener. Once opened, clicking anywhere outside the menu leaves it open. Fix: add a transparent `fixed inset-0 z-9` backdrop `div` that calls `onClose`. One-line change.

### Finding 2 (MEDIUM): Unit test gap — snooze option selection untested
`BriefingPanel.test.tsx:34` — The updated test only checks that clicking "Snooze" fires `onSnoozeToggle`. It no longer verifies that selecting "Tomorrow" calls `onSnooze('thing-1', date)`. Needs a second test with `snoozeMenuOpen={true}` asserting the selection behavior.

### Finding 3 (LOW): `waitForTimeout(500)` fixed sleep in mobile test
`visual.spec.ts:295` — Can be removed; the subsequent `waitForSelector('text=Due Today')` already provides a deterministic wait.

### Finding 4 (LOW, informational): Desktop and dark-desktop snapshots are identical
The app uses a fixed dark theme, so both screenshots capture the same state. Not blocking — the CLAUDE.md coverage contract requires both; noting for future reviewers.

**Positives**: `snoozeMenuId` toggle design is correct and clean; graceful greeting degradation when `currentUser` is null; screenshots visually confirmed correct (greeting shows first name, all sections render properly on desktop and mobile).
